    <summary>Automated semantic version bumping CLI tool with changelog generation and git integration.</summary>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency id="nodejs" version="12.0.0" />
    </dependencies>
    <description>vnxt (vx) is a lightweight CLI tool for automated semantic version bumping.

It detects the appropriate version bump type from your conventional commit message, updates package.json, creates an annotated git tag, generates a CHANGELOG.md, and optionally pushes to remote — all in one command.

## Features

- Automatic semantic version detection from commit messages
- Automatic CHANGELOG.md generation
- Git tag annotation with configurable prefix
- Pre-flight checks for clean working directory
- Dry-run mode to preview changes
- Release notes generation
- Interactive mode when no arguments provided
- Colored terminal output
- Quiet mode for CI/CD environments
- Automated npm publishing via GitHub Actions

## Usage

    vx -m "feat: add new feature"
    vx -m "fix: resolve bug"
    vx -m "BREAKING: new API structure"

## Requirements

Node.js must be installed. Install it with: `choco install nodejs`
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/n-orrow/vnxt/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md</releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
</package>